Name: ELEVATION MEASUREMENT ACCURACY
Explanation: NUMERIC VALUE GIVING THE PLUS OR MINUS ACCURACY (ABSOLUTE VALUE OF THE ERROR) TO WHICH AN ELEVATION MEASUREMENT IS EXPRESSED.

Name: ELEVATION MEASUREMENT MSL ACCURACY
Explanation: NUMERIC VALUE GIVING THE PLUS OR MINUS ACCURACY (ABSOLUTE VALUE OF THE ERROR) TO WHICH AN ELEVATION MEASUREMENT, REFERRING TO MSL, IS EXPRESSED.

Name: COORDINATES DERIVATION ACCURACY
Explanation: INDICATES THE ABSOLUTE VALUE OF THE ERROR (PLUS OR MINUS) ASSESSED AGAINST THE METHOD USED TO DERIVE THE COORDINATE. THIS DERIVATION ERROR IS USED ALONG WITH THE SOURCE ERROR AND THE RADIUS OF ACCURACY (ROA) ERROR IN ORDER TO CORRECTLY ASSESS PRECISION TARGETING COORDINATES.

Name: ELEVATION DERIVATION ACCURACY
Explanation: INDICATES THE ABSOLUTE VALUE OF THE ERROR (PLUS OR MINUS) ASSESSED AGAINST THE METHOD USED TO DERIVE THE ELEVATION. THIS DERIVATION ERROR IS USED ALONG WITH THE SOURCE ERROR IN ORDER TO CORRECTLY ASSESS A PRECISION TARGETING ELEVATION.

Name: ELEVATION MSL DERIVATION ACCURACY
Explanation: INDICATES THE ABSOLUTE VALUE OF THE ERROR (PLUS OR MINUS) ASSESSED AGAINST THE METHOD USED TO DERIVE THE ELEVATION. THIS DERIVATION ERROR IS USED ALONG WITH THE SOURCE ERROR IN ORDER TO CORRECTLY ASSESS A PRECISION TARGETING ELEVATION.
